  "instructions": [
    "1. In a large bowl, whisk together soy sauce, sake, mirin, brown sugar, grated ginger, and garlic.",
    "2. Add the thinly sliced veal to the marinade and toss to coat.",
    "3. Cover the bowl with plastic wrap and refrigerate for at least 2 hours or overnight.",
    "4. Preheat a grill or grill pan to medium-high heat.",
    "5. Thread 2-3 pieces of marinated veal onto skewers.",
    "6. Brush the grill or grill pan with sesame oil to prevent sticking.",
    "7. Grill the veal for 2-3 minutes per side, or until cooked through.",
    "8. Serve the grilled veal hot, garnished with thinly sliced scallions and smoked sesame seeds if desired.",
    "9. Serve immediately and enjoy!"
  ],
